01:19:36.730 --> 01:19:39.608
A relative, a lost love.

01:19:39.692 --> 01:19:44.488
When everyone can be found,
we can never lose a friend.

01:19:46.448 --> 01:19:48.284
We can take a suggestion
from the audience.

01:19:48.367 --> 01:19:52.371
- Uh... anyone?
- Find Mercer!

01:19:55.499 --> 01:19:57.918
I'm pretty sure
he doesn't wanna be found.

01:19:59.295 --> 01:20:00.963
- Anyone else?
- Where's Mercer?

01:20:01.046 --> 01:20:05.342
<i>No, Mae, this is what Soul Search
is all about as well as Completion.</i>

01:20:05.426 --> 01:20:06.427
Other suggestions?

01:20:06.510 --> 01:20:08.363
- Let's try Mercer.
- Mercer! Mercer! Mercer!

01:20:08.387 --> 01:20:09.406
<i>It's the whole point
of Soul Search, Mae.</i>

01:20:09.430 --> 01:20:10.264
No.

01:20:10.347 --> 01:20:12.558
Mercer! Mercer!

01:20:12.641 --> 01:20:14.536
- Mercer! Mercer! Mercer!
- No, no, no, no.

01:20:14.560 --> 01:20:16.228
No, I...

01:20:16.312 --> 01:20:18.731
<i>Mae, this is the right choice.</i>

01:20:18.814 --> 01:20:21.108
Wait. Hey, everybody.

01:20:21.191 --> 01:20:23.071
Hey.

01:20:23.610 --> 01:20:25.946
I think it's time we reunited
Mae and Mercer, don't you?

01:20:26.947 --> 01:20:29.158
All right then.
And through the power of the Circle,

01:20:29.241 --> 01:20:31.744
let's bring them
back together again, okay?

01:20:31.827 --> 01:20:35.581
The perfect use of Soul Search.
Let's find your friend.

01:20:38.167 --> 01:20:39.418
Go, Mae, now.

01:20:49.928 --> 01:20:52.389
Okay.

01:20:55.434 --> 01:21:01.607
So our second Soul Search today
involves not a fugitive from justice,

01:21:01.690 --> 01:21:04.109
but you might say a fugitive from, um...

01:21:05.444 --> 01:21:06.444
a friendship.

01:21:14.536 --> 01:21:16.372
This is my friend Mercer.

01:21:17.414 --> 01:21:20.000
I haven't seen him in a while.

01:21:20.084 --> 01:21:21.377
I'd love to see him again.

01:21:22.544 --> 01:21:27.758
Like Fiona, though, he is someone
who is trying not to be found,

01:21:27.841 --> 01:21:29.843
but unlike Fiona, he's not a criminal.

01:21:31.387 --> 01:21:32.554
He's good, people.

01:21:40.354 --> 01:21:42.194
Let's see if we can break
our previous record.

01:21:42.231 --> 01:21:43.899
Whoo!

01:22:04.753 --> 01:22:06.463
Oh, yeah.

01:22:07.464 --> 01:22:08.841
Unbelievable.

01:22:08.924 --> 01:22:10.843
Can you believe that? Yes!

01:22:13.053 --> 01:22:14.596
<i>Do you think he's in here?</i>

01:22:17.391 --> 01:22:19.184
<i>- Mercer!
- Mercer!</i>

01:22:19.268 --> 01:22:20.185
<i>Mercer, are you in there?</i>

01:22:20.269 --> 01:22:22.938
<i>Are you, like, killing deer,
making chandeliers?</i>

01:22:24.857 --> 01:22:27.710
<i>Mercer, we know you're in there.
We see your truck. It's right here.</i>

01:22:27.734 --> 01:22:29.587
<i>- I think he's in there.
- Fine. Let's go around.</i>

01:22:29.611 --> 01:22:32.865
<i>Oh, my God, he's in there!</i>

01:22:32.948 --> 01:22:34.825
<i>Mercer, come out. He's gotta be here.</i>

01:22:34.908 --> 01:22:37.119
Remember to be nice, okay?

01:22:37.202 --> 01:22:38.522
<i>Mercer, we know you're in there.</i>

01:22:38.579 --> 01:22:40.414
You found where he is. You did it.

01:22:40.497 --> 01:22:41.748
I think we should leave.

01:22:41.832 --> 01:22:44.460
<i>No, Mae, stay on this.</i>

01:22:44.543 --> 01:22:46.628
<i>You've got millions of people
enjoying this.</i>

01:22:46.712 --> 01:22:48.380
<i>There he is. There he is.</i>

01:22:48.464 --> 01:22:51.216
<i>There he is. We just got Mercer.
I cannot believe this.</i>

01:22:51.300 --> 01:22:53.020
<i>There he is! He's in the driveway!</i>

01:22:59.892 --> 01:23:01.977
<i>Leave me alone! Jesus Christ!</i>

01:23:23.415 --> 01:23:24.833
You're kidding me.

01:23:29.254 --> 01:23:31.840
Can someone please get me audio
on the camera?

01:23:33.550 --> 01:23:34.968
Mercer.

01:23:35.052 --> 01:23:38.013
Mercer, stop driving. It's just me.

01:23:38.096 --> 01:23:39.723
Mercer, stop the truck.

01:23:39.806 --> 01:23:41.934
You're surrounded by friends.

01:23:43.310 --> 01:23:45.062
Can we turn the speaker up?

01:23:46.313 --> 01:23:47.314
Mercer.

01:23:48.815 --> 01:23:49.983
Can you hear me?

01:23:51.235 --> 01:23:52.653
Mercer, it's me.

01:23:52.736 --> 01:23:54.376
You're surrounded by friends.

01:23:57.991 --> 01:23:59.952
Mercer, stop.

01:24:23.183 --> 01:24:24.851
How you doing, sweetie?

01:24:27.354 --> 01:24:29.982
You've been in bed for three days.

01:24:31.149 --> 01:24:33.986
Come out in the garden
with me today, okay?

01:24:34.069 --> 01:24:37.406
I've got some new snapdragons
that need to be planted.

01:24:38.699 --> 01:24:39.700
Okay?

01:24:40.909 --> 01:24:41.910
Honey.

01:24:45.163 --> 01:24:46.164
Oh, honey.

01:24:47.916 --> 01:24:49.501
Oh.

01:24:51.378 --> 01:24:53.922
Oh.

01:24:54.006 --> 01:24:56.526
<i>The California
Department of Motor Vehicles</i>

01:24:56.550 --> 01:24:59.177
<i>has proposed regulation
that self-driving cars</i>

01:24:59.261 --> 01:25:02.222
<i>should be required to have
a licensed driver inside.</i>

01:25:02.306 --> 01:25:03.724
<i>Is that a good principle?</i>

01:25:03.807 --> 01:25:06.643
<i>Yeah, I mean, I think obviously,</i>

01:25:06.727 --> 01:25:09.229
<i>where technology is today
that is a good principle,</i>

01:25:09.313 --> 01:25:11.708
<i>and of course, we would not suggest
putting something unsafe on the road.</i>

01:25:11.732 --> 01:25:13.191
<i>That's why we have fed...</i>

01:27:09.391 --> 01:27:10.391
<i>Mae.</i>

01:27:11.435 --> 01:27:12.811
Where are you?

01:27:12.894 --> 01:27:15.605
- Are we alone?
- Yes.

01:27:15.689 --> 01:27:16.690
Are we?

01:27:16.773 --> 01:27:17.774
Yes.

01:27:19.985 --> 01:27:22.946
How is it daytime where you are?

01:27:23.029 --> 01:27:25.407
Wait, you're in Scotland.

01:27:25.490 --> 01:27:27.993
Yep, I went home. Can you see?

01:27:29.953 --> 01:27:31.413
What happened?

01:27:31.496 --> 01:27:34.291
What, besides almost ODing
on speed and Soylent?

01:27:34.374 --> 01:27:36.126
Well, I found out I'm allergic to wheat.

01:27:39.838 --> 01:27:42.716
Um... I don't know.

01:27:42.799 --> 01:27:44.092
I guess I almost died?

01:27:47.888 --> 01:27:49.848
Oh, come on, no, don't.
Don't make me cry.

01:27:49.931 --> 01:27:52.350
Come on. No.
I'm not going to cry anymore.

01:27:54.561 --> 01:27:55.601
You getting better there?

01:27:56.646 --> 01:27:58.690
<i>Yeah, I am.</i>

01:27:58.774 --> 01:28:04.404
I eat. I look out the window.
I come out here, and I think I daydream.

01:28:04.488 --> 01:28:05.572
Hadn't done that in years.

01:28:07.073 --> 01:28:08.158
I'm glad you called.

01:28:11.286 --> 01:28:12.788
I didn't want to lose you, too.

01:28:14.331 --> 01:28:15.332
<i>I know.</i>

01:28:17.125 --> 01:28:19.419
Listen, Mae, I'm really,
really sorry about Mercer.

01:28:20.462 --> 01:28:23.298
And I'm a shit friend.
I should've said something sooner.

01:28:23.381 --> 01:28:24.758
I should've, and I'm sorry.

01:28:26.510 --> 01:28:27.719
It's just so horrible.

01:28:30.388 --> 01:28:31.890
Have they spoken to you about it?

01:28:33.225 --> 01:28:34.226
Not yet.

01:28:35.393 --> 01:28:37.020
I'm going in tomorrow.

01:28:37.103 --> 01:28:40.357
<i>Uh-huh. They ask for forgiveness
and never for permission.</i>

01:28:40.440 --> 01:28:42.526
They have to go.
They've broken a hundred laws.

01:28:42.609 --> 01:28:45.612
They've made me suffer
a thousand regulations.

01:28:45.695 --> 01:28:47.239
There's got to be a way to...

01:28:47.322 --> 01:28:49.574
What? Stop people doing bad shit?

01:28:49.658 --> 01:28:51.701
Yeah.

01:28:53.078 --> 01:28:56.289
Do you need some time away here, too?
I've got an extra bed if you want it.

01:29:00.836 --> 01:29:04.756
This feels so good, just being with you.

01:29:04.840 --> 01:29:07.384
- Even like this.
- Yeah.

01:29:08.510 --> 01:29:09.719
Yeah. I know.

01:29:13.014 --> 01:29:15.225
This is going to sound crazy. But...

01:29:15.308 --> 01:29:17.352
I keep having this feeling that...

01:29:18.395 --> 01:29:20.772
Mercer would still be here
if we hadn't lost touch.

01:29:20.856 --> 01:29:22.816
No, come on,
what were you supposed to do?

01:29:22.899 --> 01:29:25.193
I mean, you know, he drifted away.

01:29:26.194 --> 01:29:27.320
It happens.

01:29:27.404 --> 01:29:30.490
Yes, but we have this technology,
all this power.

01:29:30.574 --> 01:29:33.952
Well, I mean, technology
didn't exactly help the situation.

01:29:35.954 --> 01:29:36.955
What if it could?

01:29:43.336 --> 01:29:46.214
Hey, your dad woke up at 4:00
this morning,

01:29:46.298 --> 01:29:48.133
and your light was still on.

01:29:48.216 --> 01:29:50.802
What were you doing in your room?
Were you on the phone?

01:29:52.554 --> 01:29:54.139
It helped.

01:29:54.222 --> 01:29:56.057
I have friends all over the world.

01:29:57.475 --> 01:29:58.476
They care.

01:29:58.560 --> 01:29:59.894
Mm.

01:29:59.978 --> 01:30:03.565
- I spoke to Annie.
- How is she?

01:30:03.648 --> 01:30:05.275
Good. Better.

01:30:06.443 --> 01:30:08.111
I realized how much I missed her.

01:30:12.407 --> 01:30:14.159
I have to go back.

01:30:14.242 --> 01:30:15.660
Go back where?

01:30:18.079 --> 01:30:19.205
Not to the Circle.

01:30:19.289 --> 01:30:21.333
The Circle didn't kill Mercer, Mom.

01:30:21.416 --> 01:30:23.960
It was a bad tool, a bad system.

01:30:24.044 --> 01:30:26.963
It... It can be fixed.

01:30:28.423 --> 01:30:31.009
We're not gonna become Amish, Mom.

01:30:31.092 --> 01:30:33.720
I... When someone dies in a plane crash,

01:30:33.803 --> 01:30:37.724
you don't abandon planes,
you make them safer.

01:30:37.807 --> 01:30:39.476
Mae, at least wait a bit.

01:30:39.559 --> 01:30:41.436
I'm the only one who can do this.

01:30:42.937 --> 01:30:43.938
I'm sorry.

01:30:45.607 --> 01:30:47.108
I love you.

01:31:10.632 --> 01:31:12.926
<i>- Hello?
- Hey, it's me.</i>

01:31:13.009 --> 01:31:15.887
<i>Mae. How are you holding up?</i>

01:31:15.970 --> 01:31:18.932
<i>Better, actually.
I'm coming in to see them today.</i>

01:31:19.015 --> 01:31:22.352
<i>- But I need your help.
- Sure. Name it, anything you need.</i>

01:31:52.048 --> 01:31:54.443
We were worried
when we didn't hear from you for so long.

01:31:54.467 --> 01:31:56.219
We were very concerned.

01:31:56.302 --> 01:31:58.596
No contact for four days.
Your camera was off.

01:31:58.680 --> 01:31:59.680
How are you doing?

01:32:02.809 --> 01:32:03.809
I'm okay.

01:32:04.894 --> 01:32:06.914
Tom and I have been talking
about how little we knew

01:32:06.938 --> 01:32:08.857
about this young man Mercer.

01:32:08.940 --> 01:32:11.151
He's someone we should
have been able to help.

01:32:11.234 --> 01:32:13.987
A fund should be established
for his family.

01:32:15.113 --> 01:32:17.615
Yeah, absolutely, that's done.

01:32:17.699 --> 01:32:20.660
Listen, Mae, we would like
to offer you a new role

01:32:20.744 --> 01:32:25.415
here at the Circle
with no formal obligation,

01:32:25.498 --> 01:32:27.459
maybe a lighter schedule.

01:32:27.542 --> 01:32:30.044
You can choose your own projects,
and you can think long-term.

01:32:30.128 --> 01:32:32.464
You could take pottery, if you wanted.

01:32:32.547 --> 01:32:34.066
I don't know if you're aware of this,

01:32:34.090 --> 01:32:36.843
- but one of our founders, Ty Lafitte...
- Yeah.

01:32:36.926 --> 01:32:42.223
...was given the same opportunity,
and now he loves his freedom.

01:32:42.307 --> 01:32:45.518
And I don't know
if this is any consolation,

01:32:45.602 --> 01:32:48.980
but at our next Dream Friday...

01:32:49.063 --> 01:32:50.940
We're going to imagine a world

01:32:51.024 --> 01:32:54.736
in which every disturbed young man
could be kept safe.

01:32:56.446 --> 01:32:57.739
Would you like to join us?

01:32:59.866 --> 01:33:02.494
I'm not sure I'm ready for that. But...

01:33:04.454 --> 01:33:05.538
thanks for the invitation.

01:33:06.539 --> 01:33:07.539
Take your time.

01:33:33.191 --> 01:33:36.569
I did what you asked.
You won't believe the shit I found.

01:33:36.653 --> 01:33:41.074
It's worse than I could've imagined.
And, and look, Mae, I'm so sorry.

01:33:41.157 --> 01:33:45.036
I never met him, but they should build
a monument to Mercer.

01:33:47.288 --> 01:33:50.959
- Yeah.
- I mean, this... this changes everything.

01:33:51.042 --> 01:33:54.087
Okay, he's the martyr
who will wake everyone up, right?

01:33:54.170 --> 01:33:57.632
I don't know what you're planning,
but if you turn that camera back on,

01:33:57.715 --> 01:34:00.635
whatever you say about the Circle
is heard around the world,

01:34:00.718 --> 01:34:02.345
and it changes everything.

01:34:17.735 --> 01:34:18.735
<i>Hello</i>.

01:34:22.407 --> 01:34:23.408
Hello again.

01:34:29.122 --> 01:34:30.456
<i>- Hi!
- Hey, Mae.</i>

01:34:39.924 --> 01:34:41.634
And that is how it should have been,

01:34:41.718 --> 01:34:44.220
how it could've been,
but we didn't have the technology.

01:34:44.304 --> 01:34:45.555
But we will.

01:34:45.638 --> 01:34:47.015
And when we do,

01:34:47.098 --> 01:34:50.393
when every vehicle
is known and connected,

01:34:50.476 --> 01:34:53.813
the data we have will help us
improve traffic patterns,

01:34:53.897 --> 01:35:00.486
keep drivers safe, and optimize
Circle services across all platforms.

01:35:00.570 --> 01:35:03.698
Shopping. Lodging.

01:35:03.781 --> 01:35:05.325
Attractions.

01:35:06.367 --> 01:35:08.036
Attractions like Mae Holland.

01:35:08.119 --> 01:35:09.799
Mae, come on out here.

01:35:09.871 --> 01:35:12.248
<i>Come on out here. Gosh, Mae.</i>

01:35:12.332 --> 01:35:14.667
<i>Oh, you're transparent again.
Look at that.</i>

01:35:14.751 --> 01:35:16.920
Hello, hello.

01:35:17.003 --> 01:35:18.003
Mae Holland.

01:35:18.046 --> 01:35:21.549
Welcome back, Mae!

01:35:21.633 --> 01:35:27.013
Now, Mae is a brave person

01:35:27.096 --> 01:35:28.932
because even amid her grieving,

01:35:29.015 --> 01:35:33.853
she knows that she has a responsibility
to her followers,

01:35:33.937 --> 01:35:35.480
to the whole world, really.

01:35:37.065 --> 01:35:41.486
Thanks for saying that, Eamon.
And I couldn't agree with you more.

01:35:42.904 --> 01:35:45.823
I know that Tom, he agrees, too.

01:35:45.907 --> 01:35:49.994
Right, Tom? You want to come out?

01:35:50.078 --> 01:35:52.705
- Come on.
- There you are.

01:35:56.668 --> 01:36:00.171
First, I want to thank everyone here
and around the world

01:36:00.254 --> 01:36:03.591
for the support you've given me
since we lost Mercer.

01:36:03.675 --> 01:36:08.429
These past days,
I've realized something about myself

01:36:08.513 --> 01:36:09.681
and about the Circle.

01:36:10.848 --> 01:36:13.184
It's that I don't want to be disconnected.

01:36:14.602 --> 01:36:18.564
I don't want to have to search
for friends, family, my loved ones.

01:36:19.774 --> 01:36:21.275
We lost track of Mercer.

01:36:22.819 --> 01:36:25.405
But what if we never lost touch
with each other?

01:36:27.615 --> 01:36:29.409
What if instead of searching...

01:36:30.743 --> 01:36:31.911
we always knew?

01:36:34.038 --> 01:36:38.960
What I am proposing is radical openness
and unbroken connection.

01:36:41.713 --> 01:36:43.673
It would have to start here.

01:36:43.756 --> 01:36:45.425
Mm-hm.

01:36:45.508 --> 01:36:48.886
You know the usual hypocrisy
of the digital world.

01:36:48.970 --> 01:36:53.141
We want everything in the Cloud,
and yet our leaders...

01:36:55.101 --> 01:36:56.936
live above it.

01:36:57.020 --> 01:37:01.649
So I want to invite Eamon and Tom

01:37:01.733 --> 01:37:06.112
to join me in this experiment
that they've pioneered.

01:37:07.739 --> 01:37:13.494
I invite them to set an example
for the Circle and the world...

01:37:16.581 --> 01:37:18.124
to go transparent.

01:37:22.837 --> 01:37:24.422
What do you say, guys?

01:37:26.424 --> 01:37:27.425
Will you join me?

01:37:34.557 --> 01:37:38.561
Wouldn't it be great to know
their every move, their every word?

01:37:38.644 --> 01:37:43.024
From now on,
every message, meeting, phone call,

01:37:43.107 --> 01:37:48.362
all will be public,
knowable, never erased.

01:37:49.530 --> 01:37:51.699
In fact, Ty Lafitte has helped us
make every document

01:37:51.783 --> 01:37:55.411
in the company's history public.

01:37:55.495 --> 01:37:58.039
Every message, every plan including...

01:37:58.122 --> 01:38:01.375
And this is my favorite part,
every e-mail,

01:38:01.459 --> 01:38:05.505
from Tom and Eamon's accounts,
and their private accounts...

01:38:06.506 --> 01:38:08.692
...and their secondary
confidential accounts.

01:38:08.716 --> 01:38:12.678
And even their super-secret
scrambled code accounts,

01:38:12.762 --> 01:38:18.684
that nobody, not even their assistants
or wives knew existed.

01:38:20.186 --> 01:38:21.312
Until now.

01:38:24.273 --> 01:38:26.150
It's all been sent to you already.

01:38:29.821 --> 01:38:31.989
We are so fucked.

01:38:32.073 --> 01:38:35.993
I think we're entitled
to that kind of access. Don't you?

01:38:36.077 --> 01:38:39.497
Yeah.

01:38:40.623 --> 01:38:42.792
Mae, you are a very brave woman
to do this.

01:38:48.673 --> 01:38:51.759
There are no more secrets.

01:38:51.843 --> 01:38:53.594
Privacy was a temporary thing.

01:38:54.804 --> 01:38:55.888
And now it's over.

01:38:57.640 --> 01:38:59.809
We won't live in the shadows anymore.

01:39:01.227 --> 01:39:03.437
Hey. Good timing.

01:39:22.999 --> 01:39:24.000
Thank you.

01:39:25.251 --> 01:39:26.919
Thank you.

01:39:27.003 --> 01:39:33.968
I'm tired of hiding,
these passwords and secret knocks,

01:39:34.051 --> 01:39:36.846
the difference between public and private.

01:39:38.472 --> 01:39:39.515
Aren't you all?

01:39:40.933 --> 01:39:42.894
Come to think of it,

01:39:42.977 --> 01:39:44.896
I'm tired of standing here in the dark.

01:39:46.856 --> 01:39:48.065
Don't worry.

01:39:48.149 --> 01:39:52.945
Eamon will catch up. Or maybe he won't.

01:39:53.029 --> 01:39:55.781
Either way, it's time for a change.

01:39:55.865 --> 01:39:57.783
We're gonna remake this place.

01:39:57.867 --> 01:40:03.456
And if we do it right,
we will set an example for everyone.

01:40:03.539 --> 01:40:05.124
